liquid interface, all conspire to cause the anomalously poor\nwetting of the (100) surface by its own melt in the BMHFT model of NaCl -- and\nmost likely also in real alkali halide surfaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Dec 2005 18:29:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
